description:
&lt;p&gt;To provide care management intervention with a client group; working aged adults open to forensic services across specialism e.g. Learning Disability. Working within a specialist forensic team where a diverse range and complexity of issues are presented. Seeking guidance when required and formal supervision from line manager, in line with departmental policy.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To role model compassionate and creative interventions. This means demonstrating a consistent style which (a) engages, enables and empowers others (b) uses coaching to promote ownership of learning and quality improvement and (c) facilitates team working and collaboration within teams / departments and across organisational boundaries.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Essential Criteria:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Knowledge acquired through inhouse training, short course and experience to NVQ 3 level or equivalent plus knowledge of specific patient conditions, forms of therapy, acquired through training, experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Working with adults in a social care setting.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Adult and child protection.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Benefits systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Legislation relevant to mental health &amp; adult social care.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mental illness&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Andrew Ball&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Forensic Team Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: andrew.ball@northumbria-healthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number:01670 536400&lt;/p&gt;
